    <!-- About Tab -->
    <string name="tab_about">About App</string>
    <string name="about_subtitle">Understanding anti-censorship mechanisms and relay system operations</string>
    <string name="about_title">What is Lion VPN and how does it work?</string>
    <string name="about_description">This app repackages your internet traffic and sends it as standard HTTP requests to Google servers. Since Google servers and domains are generally not blocked, this traffic passes through censorship barriers without hindrance.

Then, on the Google side (via the script deployed in your Google account), this package is opened (depackaged) and forwarded to the target server. Upon receiving the response from the destination, the Google server repackages it and sends it back to the app. This process acts exactly like a VPN, allowing you to access blocked websites seamlessly.</string>
    <string name="about_features_title">Key Benefits:</string>
    <string name="about_feature_1">⚡ Secure bypass using stable Google Infrastructure</string>
    <string name="about_feature_2">🔒 Highly resilient to blocking because it uses official Google domains</string>
    <string name="about_feature_3">🛠️ Full control over the proxy server (your personal Google Apps Script)</string>

    <!-- About Limits Box -->
    <string name="about_limits_title">Google Consumption Limits and How to Bypass Them</string>
    <string name="about_limits_description">Google imposes daily rate limits on the free Apps Script service. If your usage exceeds this limit, the Google server will temporarily stop responding.

To fully bypass this, you can create multiple deployments on one or more Google accounts. If you encounter this limit, simply go to "Scripts" and switch your active Deployment ID to another one to continue browsing uninterrupted.</string>

